OL,3,CNo evidence former police chief misled
OL,4,CGuernsey's Royal Court
OL,6,FA statement from The Committee for
OL,7,FHome Affairs reads: "Former CO Hardy
OL,8,Fserved Guernsey Police as a
OL,10,Fdedicated leader for nearly six years,
OL,11,Fand retired last year, concluding a
OL,12,Fcareer in which he gave excellent
OL,13,Fsupport and leadership to the
OL,14,FBailiwick community.
OL,16,F"It is the Committee for Home Affairs'
OL,17,Fview that the Bailiwick must have a
OL,18,Frobust and trusted police complaints
OL,19,Fsystem, and all complaints against
OL,20,Fpolice officers must be taken
OL,21,Fseriously.
